     A Curated List of Ruby Machine Learning Links and Resources

   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning]Machine Learning is a
   field of
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_science]Computational
   Science - often nested under
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence]AI research -
   with many practical applications due to the ability of resulting
   algorithms to systematically implement a specific solution without
   explicit programmer's instructions. Obviously many algorithms need a
   definition of
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Feature_engineering]features to look at
   or a biggish [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_set]training set of
   data to derive the solution from.

   This curated list comprises
   [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome/blob/master/awesome.md]awesome
   libraries, data sources, tutorials and presentations about
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning]Machine Learning
   utilizing the [https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/]Ruby programming language.

   A lot of useful resources on this list come from the development by
   [https://github.com/sciruby]The Ruby Science Foundation, our
   [https://github.com/arbox/machine-learning-with-ruby/graphs/contributor
   s]contributors and our own day to day work on various ML applications.
   Read
   [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/machine-learning-
   with-ruby#wait-but-why]why this list is awesome.

   ¨ Every
   [file://localhost/arbox/machine-learning-with-ruby/blob/master/contribu
   ting.md]contribution is welcome! Add links through pull requests or
   create an issue to start a discussion.

   Follow us on [https://twitter.com/NonWebRuby]Twitter and please spread
   the word using the #RubyML hash tag!

