     * [https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench/blob/master/ex
       amples/neuroevolution.rb]How to evolve neural networks in Ruby
       using the Machine Learning Workbench

Machine Learning Libraries

   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning]Machine Learning
   algorithms in pure Ruby or written in other programming languages with
   appropriate bindings for Ruby.

Frameworks

     * [https://github.com/paulgoetze/weka-jruby]weka - JRuby bindings for
       Weka, different ML algorithms implemented through Weka.
     * [https://github.com/SergioFierens/ai4r]ai4r - Artificial
       Intelligence for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/jekyll/classifier-reborn]classifier-reborn -
       General classifier module to allow Bayesian and other types of
       classifications.
       ^[
     * [https://github.com/asafschers/scoruby]scoruby - Ruby scoring API
       for [http://dmg.org/pmml/v4-3/GeneralStructure.html]PMML
       (Predictive Model Markup Language).
     * [https://github.com/himkt/rblearn]rblearn - Feature Extraction and
       Crossvalidation library.
     * [https://github.com/giuse/data_modeler]data_modeler - Model your
       data with machine learning. Ample test coverage, examples to start
       fast, complete documentation. Production ready since 1.0.0.
     * [https://github.com/shogun-toolbox/shogun]shogun - Polyfunctional
       and mature machine learning toolbox with
       [https://github.com/shogun-toolbox/shogun/tree/develop/src/interfac
       es/ruby]Ruby bindings and enormous
       [http://www.shogun-toolbox.org/examples/latest/examples/regression/
       random_forest_regression.html]documentation.
     * [https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-ruby]aws-sdk-machinelearning -
       Machine Learning API of the Amazon Web Services.
     * [https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-ruby]azure_mgmt_machine_lea
       rning - Machine Learning API of the Microsoft Azure.
     * [https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench]machine_learni
       ng_workbench - Growing machine learning framework written in pure
       Ruby, high performance computing using
       [https://github.com/ruby-numo/]Numo, CUDA bindings through
       [https://github.com/sonots/cumo]Cumo. Currently implementating
       neural networks, evolutionary strategies, vector quantization, and
       plenty of examples and utilities.
     * [https://github.com/giuse/DNE]Deep NeuroEvolution - Experimental
       setup based on the
       [https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench]machine_learni
       ng_workbench towards searching for deep neural networks (rather
       than training) using evolutionary algorithms. Applications to the
       [https://github.com/openai/gym]OpenAI Gym using
       [https://github.com/mrkn/pycall.rb]PyCall.

Neural networks

     * [https://github.com/gbuesing/neural-net-ruby]neural-net-ruby -
       Neural network written in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/tangledpath/ruby-fann]ruby-fann - Ruby bindings
       to the [http://leenissen.dk/fann/wp/]Fast Artificial Neural Network
       Library (FANN).
     * [https://github.com/irfansharif/cerebrum]cerebrum - Experimental
       implementation for Artificial Neural Networks in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/josephwilk/tlearn-rb]tlearn-rb - Recurrent
       Neural Network library for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/jedld/brains-jruby]brains - Feed-forward neural
       networks for JRuby based on
       [https://github.com/jedld/brains]brains.
     * [https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench/tree/master/li
       b/machine_learning_workbench/neural_network]machine_learning_workbe
       nch - Framework including pure-Ruby implementation of both
       feed-forward and recurrent neural networks (fully connected).
       Training available using neuroevolution (Natural Evolution
       Strategies algorithms).
     * [https://github.com/mikecmpbll/rann]rann - Flexible Ruby ANN
       implementation with backprop (through-time, for recurrent nets),
       gradient checking, adagrad, and parallel batch execution.

Kernel methods

     * [https://github.com/febeling/rb-libsvm]rb-libsvm - Support Vector
       Machines with Ruby and the
       [https://www.csie.ntu.edu.tw/%7Ecjlin/libsvm/]LIBSVM library.
       ^[

Evolutionary algorithms

     * [https://github.com/giuse/machine_learning_workbench/tree/master/li
       b/machine_learning_workbench/optimizer/natural_evolution_strategies
       ]machine_learning_workbench - Framework including pure-Ruby
       implementations of Natural Evolution Strategy algorithms (black-box
       optimization), specifically Exponential NES (XNES), Separable NES
       (sNES), Block-Diagonal NES (BDNES) and more. Applications include
       neural network search/training (neuroevolution).
     * [https://github.com/giuse/simple_ga]simple_ga - Simplest Genetic
       Algorithms implementation in Ruby.

Bayesian methods

     * [https://github.com/djcp/linnaeus]linnaeus - Redis-backed Bayesian
       classifier.
     * [https://github.com/reddavis/Naive-Bayes]naive_bayes - Simple Naive
       Bayes classifier.
     * [https://github.com/oasic/nbayes]nbayes - Full-featured, Ruby
       implementation of Naive Bayes.

Decision trees

     * [https://github.com/igrigorik/decisiontree]decisiontree - Decision
       Tree ID3 Algorithm in pure Ruby.
       ^[dep: GraphViz |
       [https://www.igvita.com/2007/04/16/decision-tree-learning-in-ruby/]
       post].

Clustering

     * [https://github.com/mariusmuja/flann]flann - Fast Library for
       Approximate Nearest Neighbors.
       ^[[file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/machine-lea
       rning-with-ruby#flann]flann]
     * [https://github.com/gbuesing/kmeans-clusterer]kmeans-clusterer -
       k-means clustering in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/reddavis/K-Means]k_means - Attempting to build
       a fast, memory efficient K-Means program.
     * [https://github.com/reddavis/knn]knn - Simple K Nearest Neighbour
       Algorithm.

Linear classifiers

     * [https://github.com/tomz/liblinear-ruby-swig]liblinear-ruby-swig -
       Ruby interface to LIBLINEAR (much more efficient than LIBSVM for
       text classification).
     * [https://github.com/kei500/liblinear-ruby]liblinear-ruby - Ruby
       interface to LIBLINEAR using SWIG.

Statistical models

     * [https://github.com/maspwr/rtimbl]rtimbl - Memory based learners
       from the Timbl framework.
     * [https://github.com/ealdent/lda-ruby]lda-ruby - Ruby implementation
       of the
       [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latent_Dirichlet_allocation]LDA
       (Latent Dirichlet Allocation) for automatic Topic Modelling and
       Document Clustering.
     * [https://github.com/mccraigmccraig/maxent_string_classifier]maxent_
       string_classifier - JRuby maximum entropy classifier for string
       data, based on the OpenNLP Maxent framework.
     * [https://github.com/mustafaturan/omnicat]omnicat - Generalized rack
       framework for text classifications.
     * [https://github.com/mustafaturan/omnicat-bayes]omnicat-bayes -
       Naive Bayes text classification implementation as an OmniCat
       classifier strategy.
       ^[[file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/machine-lea
       rning-with-ruby#bundled]dep: bundled]

Applications of machine learning

     * [https://github.com/westonplatter/phashion]phashion - Ruby wrapper
       around pHash, the perceptual hash library for detecting duplicate
       multimedia files.
       ^[[file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/machine-lea
       rning-with-ruby#imagemagick]ImageMagick |
       [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/machine-learn
       ing-with-ruby#libjpeg]libjpeg]

Data structures

   If you're going to implement your own ML algorithms you're probably
   interested in storing your feature sets efficiently. Look for
   appropriate
   [https://github.com/arbox/data-science-with-ruby#data-structures]data
   structures in our [https://github.com/arbox/data-science-with-ruby]Data
   Science with Ruby list.

Data visualization

   Please refer to the
   [https://github.com/arbox/data-science-with-ruby#visualization]Data
   Visualization section on the
   [https://github.com/arbox/data-science-with-ruby]Data Science with Ruby
   list.

